          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p>Original via <placeName>New York</placeName>.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">
                                        <placeName>Pto. Cabello</placeName>
                                        <date>April 24<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1854</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Isaac Leeser Esq.</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <placeName>Philada.</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p>Dear Sir!</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Your valued lines <date>21<hi rend="sup"
                                                  >st</hi></date> utlo. covering Invoice<lb/> &amp;
                                        B/L ading<add>?</add> for one box books are at hand.</p>
                              <p>The “Dallett” is still in <placeName>La Guayra</placeName>, but I
                                        have written by<lb/> opportunity to <persName>Messrs Dovale
                                                  &amp; Co.</persName> of <placeName>New
                                                  York</placeName>, to place<lb/> at your disposal,
                                        and if possible to have the amt of $69.93<lb/> handed to you
                                        personally, by any of their friends in
                                                  <placeName>Philada</placeName>.<lb/> I enclose
                                        second of exchange for the $69.38, the first of<lb/> which I
                                        trust have reached you long ere this.</p>
                              <p>I will avail myself of this pleasure again by first<lb/>
                                        opportunity Meanwhile accept my warmest thanks<lb/> for the
                                        service rendered to me in procuring the books, and<lb/>
                                        believe me, Dear Sir, Yours faithfully <persName
                                                  role="author">A Myerston</persName></p>
                              <p>Dear Sir,</p>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <date>April 28<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1854</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>The above is dupe of my last respects, and far from<lb/> returning
                                        the copies of the Jewish miscellany and<lb/> your own
                                        discourses I beg to return you many thanks<lb/> for having
                                        sent them. I remain in haste Yrs Respectfully</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <persName role="author">A Myerston</persName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>
                                        <hi rend="underline">“<persName>Thomas
                                                  Dallett</persName>”</hi>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">Received</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">
                                        <date>May 15</date>
                              </p>
                              <p><addressee>Isaac Leeser Esq</addressee>:</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>No. 371 Walnut St.</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>
                                                  <hi rend="underline">Philadelphia</hi>
                                        </placeName>
                              </p>
